SIMPLE: minded
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Minded
<hw>Mind"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Disposed; inclined; having a
mind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Joseph . . . was <qex>minded</qex> to put her away privily.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. i. 19.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If men were <qex>minded</qex> to live virtuously.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Minded</xex> is much used in composition; as,
high-<xex>minded</xex>, feeble-<xex>minded</xex>,
bloody-<xex>minded</xex>, sober-<xex>minded</xex>,
double-<xex>minded</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minden</ent>⟦br⟧
